records.addlTxt:
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 15 CF 72, to commence upon defendants discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) have no contact with the victims family;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) no contact with any known drug users or dealers;
6) maintain fulltime employment or work search as directed by the agent;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) Comply with electronic monitoring if approved/ordered.
Minutes.
